President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate Derek J. Mitchell as Ambassador to the Union of Burma, Department of State. Mitchell is currently serving as Special Representative and Policy Coordinator for Burma and has previously held various positions in the Department of Defense and the Center for Strategic and International Studies. 

President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Anhlan P. Nguyen and Quyen N. Vuong as members of the Board of Directors of the Vietnam Education Foundation. Nguyen is currently an IT project portfolio manager at the University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center and has been involved in various leadership and community development activities. Vuong is the Executive Director of the International Children Assistance Network and is also involved in various organizations and boards.